               <p>JOSEPH STEFFANONI. I am an <rs id="t18320906-459-viclabel2589" type="occupation">upholsterer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-459-victim3676 t18320906-459-viclabel2589"></join>, and live at Holborn-bars. On the 18th of July I was near <placeName id="t18320906-459-crimeloc2590">Red Lion-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-459-crimeloc2590" type="placeName" value="Red Lion-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-459-crimeloc2590" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-459-off2587 t18320906-459-crimeloc2590"></join>; I felt a hand in my coat pocket - I turned, and took hold of the prisoner; I charged him with stealing my snuffbox, which I had just missed; he said he had not got it, but he put his hand behind him, and threw the box into the middle of Holborn.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. There were three or four more persons there. Witness. I did not see them; I believe there was one more, but I am certain the prisoner threw it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-459-person3677">
                  JOHN 
                  VAUGHAN
               <interp inst="t18320906-459-person3677" type="surname" value="VAUGHAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-459-person3677" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-459-person3677" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a horse-dealer, and live in Providence-place, Finsbury. I was with the prosecutor, and when he seized the prisoner I saw him throw the box behind him; a gentleman took it up.</p>
               <p>THOMAS BUTTRESS (Police-constable E 142.) I took the prisoner, and have the box.</p>
